, and the willingness of elites to alter their attitude to violence if it is an instrument to achieve their own ends.The interdisciplinary approach, which spans history, sociology, international law and International Relations, ensures that this book will be invaluable to a broad cross-section of scholars and politically engaged readers alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPolitical violence. 0aState-sponsored terrorism. 4aSecurity, Conflict & Peace 2018. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Diplomacy.2bisacsh  aConflict.  aGlobalisation.  aOrganised violence.  aThe state.  aWar.1 aBrostrom, Jannika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaly, Gavin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerd, Graeme P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKillingsworth, Matt, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKillingsworth, Matt, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNarramore, Terry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPakulski, Jan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPakulski, Jan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSussex, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSussex, Matthew, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWestendorf, Jasmine-Kim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2015 eBook-Packagez978311128311140uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978178499716840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781784997168423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781784997168/original  a978-3-11-128311-1  M